dct_title_s: Indiana, 1950: age-sex pyramids for for places over 10,000 in 1940
dct_description_sm: JFH.' Pen and ink. 'The numbers indicate the 1950 population of each place to the closest ten thousand.' Includes an age-sex pyramid for each of the 35 places (identified by initials) in Indiana that had a population over 10,000 in 1940. Scale not given.
dct_rights_sm: This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
